Package pacman.board

Class PacmanBoard

  • Object
    • PacmanBoard
  • public class PacmanBoard
extends Object
    PacmanBoard

    Represents the Pac Man game board. The board can be any size, it is set out as a grid with each space containing only one BoardItem. Game boards are by default surrounded by a BoardItem.WALL with every other space being BoardItem.NONE. Example: a board with width 1 and height 1 would look like this: 

         X
    A board with width 4 and height 4 would look like this: 
         XXXX
     X00X
     X00X
     XXXX
    The coordinate positions for the board is the top left position is (0, 0) and the bottom right position is (getWidth-1, getHeight-1).
    Implement this for Assignment 1

      • setEntry

        public void setEntry​(Position position,
                     BoardItem item)
              throws IndexOutOfBoundsException,
                     NullPointerException
        Sets a tile on the board to an item. If the item to be set is a BoardItem.PACMAN_SPAWN and the board already contains a BoardItem.PACMAN_SPAWN then the old BoardItem.PACMAN_SPAWN should be made a BoardItem.NONE. If the item to be set is a BoardItem.GHOST_SPAWN and the board already contains a BoardItem.GHOST_SPAWN then the old BoardItem.GHOST_SPAWN should be made a BoardItem.NONE.
        Parameters:
        item - the board item that is to be placed at the position.
        position - the portion to place the item.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - when the position trying to be set is not within the board.
        NullPointerException - when the position or item is null.
        See Also:
        Position
        Implement this for Assignment 1

      • eatDot

        public BoardItem eatDot​(Position position)
                 throws IndexOutOfBoundsException,
                        NullPointerException
        Tries to eat a dot off the board and returns the item that it ate/tried to eat. If a BoardItem.DOT is eaten then it is replaced with a BoardItem.NONE. If a BoardItem.BIG_DOT is eaten then it is replaced with a BoardItem.BIG_DOT_SPAWN. If the item is any other BoardItem then do nothing and return the item.
        Parameters:
        position - to eat.
        Returns:
        the item that was originally the position before trying to eat.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if position is null.
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - when the position trying to be eaten is not within the board.
        Implement this for Assignment 1
